29/12/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski said Tuesday (28 December) that 2005 would be a key year for Macedonia's NATO membership bid. He said the success of domestic institutions in implementing reforms would be the main factor in determining whether Skopje receives a long-awaited invitation to join the Alliance in 2007. Manasievski added that President Branko Crvenkovski will soon sign a crucial decree on restructuring the army.
In other news Tuesday, Dragan Malinovski was appointed the new chairman of Macedonia's State Anti-Corruption Commission. A member of the commission, Malinovski is replacing Jovan Tpenovski, whose one-year mandate as chief has expired. (Dnevnik, Makfax, A1 TV - 29/12/04; A1 TV - 28/12/04)
